International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Fri 28 Jun 2013
Source: Diario do Para [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.MPP, edited]
http://www.diariodopara.com.br/N-169800-EVANDRO+CHAGAS+INVESTIGA+SURTO+DE+TOXOPLASMOSE.html


A team of researchers and technicians of the Instituto Evandro Chagas (IEC) has been in Ponta de Pedras, in Marajo [Para state], since last Monday [17 Jun 2013] conducting an epidemiological investigation of an outbreak of toxoplasmosis. "It is important to make clear that, in practice, the outbreak has already occurred."

"What we are still having is some people with persistent clinical manifestations that are awaiting test results," explains the team coordinator of the IEC's work in Ponta de Pedras, Dr. Ediclei Lima do Carmo.

Epidemiological research is a field study conducted from diagnosed or suspected cases, and also people who had contact with the areas of occurrence but who are not ill.

The main objectives are to identify evidence of a possible source of infection, the most vulnerable groups, and risk factors, as well as confirm the diagnosis and determine the main epidemiological characteristics. Its ultimate purpose is to guide control measures to minimize the possibility of new outbreaks.

--
